# What should we demand going forward?

Ultimately, we present the above data in an effort to shift the conversation for solving climate change away from individual action (however important it may be) towards corporate action.

First and foremost, we demand that fossil fuel companies stop misinforming the public about the severity of climate change, including their own role in bringing it about. The first concrete step involves publicly accepting responsibility for decades of dangerous and irresponsible emissions. It goes without saying that companies must stop funding front groups and public relations spin doctors to divert attention away from the fundamental issues at hand.

Corporations must immediately cut carbon emissions from current operations and stop dangerous practices like flaring natural gas. Many fossil fuel corporations have yet to make concrete commitments to curb emissions or set dates by which they will become carbon neutral.

[Desktop]
